386→                        <div id="content">Fix some integer $n$ and define a decreasing sequence in $[1,n)$ by $a_1=n-1$ and, for $k\geq 2$, letting $a_k$ be the greatest integer in $[1,a_{k-1})$ such that all of the prime factors of $a_k$ are $&#62;n-a_k$.<br><br>Is it true that, for sufficiently large $n$, not all of this sequence can be prime?</div>
